snippet.textDisplay:
I love how she's not the best dancer, that she opts out of some of the moves in favor or vocal integrity, and most importantly: she looks likes she's genuinely enjoying herself on stage performing.


Like: I adore artists like Ariana Grande but because she a much softer voice, when she goes too into the choreography she loses a lot of vocal integrity (losing breath, going off pitch, etc)...I appreciate it when an artist knows their limits and knows/is willing to work around that while also putting on an impressive show.
Artists like Dua Lupa or Tori Kelly are phenomenal writers/singers... but not really made for the stage... Tori's a straight vocalist that hasn't quite conquered having an actual stage presence yet and Dua Lupa is, I'm proud to say, finally getting to the point where she's doesn't look completely traumatized about performing on stage/is far more confident doing choreography...


...I don't quite know where this is going so I'll just say this: Mabel is an absolute powerhouse vocalist and performer and I think her style of just having fun, taking advantage of having a choreography to better "own" the stage, while also knowing to prioritize vocals...I think that's all a good influence on incoming performers and successful artists alike.
